Chinese activist Li Guizhi was
stopped at the Hong Kong border when she tried to enter the city
to join the annual protest on July 1, the  South China Morning
Post  reported, citing Li.  The activist was then tracked down and held by Chinese
police at a hotel basement in  Hebei province , until she escaped
to an unspecified location with the help of Hong Kong-based
Peopleâ€™s Right of Union of China, SCMP reported.  Li, 57, wanted to go to Hong Kong to speak out about the
